description: From Middle English parrok, from Old English pearruc, pearroc (“clatrum, fence by which a space is enclosed, enclosure, enclosed land”). See park.

entries.meaning: (UK, dialect) An enclosure; a park; a croft, or small field; a paddock.

description: From Middle English parroken, parrokken, from parrok. See above.

verbs.description: parrock (third-person singular simple present parrocks, present participle parrocking, simple past and past participle parrocked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To enclose or shut in; park.
